HEADWORD: Lombar-house
<hw>Lom"bar-house`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <ety>[F. or D. <ets>lombard</ets>. See
<er>Lombard</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bank or a
pawnbroker's shop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A public institution for lending money to the poor
at a moderate interest, upon articles deposited and pledged; -- called
also <altname>mont de pi⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lombardic</ent>⟦br⟧
